snippet: On his high school field, Mike Catapano took the next step to becoming this year’s most unlikely draft pick, the first to be picked from Princeton in a dozen years.
abstract: Princeton defensive end Mike Catapano takes next step to becoming 2013’s most unlikely NFL draft pick, first to be picked from Princeton in dozen years; despite his impressive stats and award as Ivy League’s best defensive player as a senior, his draft preparation rarely follows same script as those from college football powers.
lead_paragraph: On his high school field, Mike Catapano took the next step to becoming this year’s most unlikely draft pick, the first to be picked from Princeton in a dozen years.

headline.seo: From Princeton, a Promising N.F.L. Draft Pick, Mike Catapano
headline.main: Unlikely Source Has Produced an N.F.L. Draft Prospect
